Normally the pizza is decent. I ordered a Caesar salad tonight and thought to share it between three people. For $12.25 one would expect it to be an entree size. Imagine my shock when I received a tiny box with a handful of lettuce.  Granted I asked for no croutons, but NO ONE HAS ANY BUSINESS CHARGING THIS MUCH FOR A HANDFUL OF ROMAINE LETTUCE! BUYER BEWARE.  I called back and they verified that this  was the price for this size salad. The quality of this place has really gone downhill in the last couple of years.  It used to have great pizza and other entrees. Now it is quite different.  I called again to ask them to pick it back up for a refund and spoke to someone who seemed to have more sense. They gave me a full refund for the salad.   However - beware of what you will receive for this price.
